import pandas as pd
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/refs/heads/master/data/2024/2024-10-15/orcas.csv"
orcas = pd.read_csv(url)
# get distinct pod values in orcas
pod_counts = orcas['pods_or_ecotype'].value_counts(ascending=False)
#pod_counts[0:10]
from random import uniform
locations=[[uniform(-80, 80), uniform(-180, 180), uniform(0, 1000)] for i in range(10)]
#locations
# Function to get colour based on pods
# J, K, L, or Bigg's Transients.
def getColour(pods):
    if pods == "Transients":
        return "green"
    if pods == "Bigg's killer whales":
        return "red"
    elif pods == "J, K, L" :
        return "blue"
    elif pods == "J, L" :
        return "orange"
    elif pods == "L" :
        return "purple"
    elif pods == "J" or pods == "J pod" or pods == "J Pod" :
        return "turquoise"
    else :
        return "gray"
from ipyleaflet import Map, Polyline

m = Map(center = [48.4, -123.8], zoom = 8)
# loop through sightings and plot
for index, row in orcas.iterrows():
    line = Polyline(
    locations=[
        [row['begin_latitude'], row['begin_longitude']],
        [row['end_latitude'], row['end_longitude']],
    ],
    color = getColour(row['pods_or_ecotype']),
    weight = 1
    )
    m.add(line)
